Package: CATFISHR
Title: CNV And Transcriptome Framework for Identification of Similarity to High-confidence References
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Prachi", "Shukla", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "prachi.shukla@usz.ch")
Description: Identifies malignant cells in single-cell and spatial transcriptomic data
    by integrating RNA expression and inferred copy number variation
    (CNV). Mahalanobis distances are measured from cells to high-confidence reference 
    centroids in both RNA and CNV PCA spaces, then jointly clustered using mean 
    shift to separate malignant from non-malignant components.
